\p
\v 1 \add This letter is from\add* Paul a prisoner of messiah Yeshua and our brother Timothy. \add I'm writing\add* to our dear co-worker Philemon,
\v 2 \x + \xo 2: \xt Col 4:17.\x*as well as \add our\add* sister Apphia and our fellow-soldier Archippus and to the assembly \add that meets\add* in your home.
\p
\v 3 \add May you all experience\add* grace and peace from our father God and from the master, Yeshua \add the\add* messiah.
\s1 Paul's prayer and gratefulness
\rem /s1 Paul's Thanksgiving and Prayer
\rem /s1 Thanksgiving and Prayer
\rem /s1 Philemon's Love and Faith
\p
\v 4 I'm always thanking my God and mentioning you in my prayers
\v 5 \add after\add* hearing your faith and about your love for the master Yeshua and for all the believers.
\v 6 \add I pray that\add* the fellowship of your faith may become active in the knowledge of every good thing in us toward \add the\add* messiah. [WHAT DOES THAT MEAN???]
\v 7 Because I was very happy and encouraged by your love, because the hearts of the believers have been refreshed by you, brother.
\s1 Paul's request to Philemon concerning Onesimus
\rem /s1 A Request for Onesimus
\rem /s1 Paul's Plea for Onesimus
\rem /s1 Paul's Appeal for Onesimus
\rem /s1 A runaway slave
\p
\v 8 Therefore, with the help of the messiah, I would be brave enough to tell you what you need to do,
\v 9 but because of love as Paul, an older man and now also a prisoner for Yeshua the messiah, I'm just going to encourage you to do it.
\v 10 \x + \xo 10: \xt Col 4:9.\x*So I'm going to encourage you concerning Onesimus who became my \add spiritual\add* ‘son’ since I've been imprisoned.
\v 11 Before he was useless to you, but now he's useful to both of us.
\p
\v 12  I sent him to you (even though in my heart
\v 13 I wanted to keep him \add here\add*) so that he might be serving me \add here due to\add* the bonds of the good message
\v 14 but I didn't want to do anything without \add hearing\add* your opinion, so that you're not doing good because you have to, but rather because you want to.
\p
