\p
\v 17 Therefore, if you consider me as your partner, accept him like you'd accept me,
\v 18 but if he did anything wrong to you or owes you anything, charge it to me.
\v 19 I, Paul, wrote this bit in my own handwriting. I will pay back anything \add he owes you\add*, then I won't need to be reminding you that you \add pretty much\add* owe yourself to me.
\v 20 Yes, brother, \add with both of us being\add* in the master, I might \add hopefully\add* benefit from you—refresh my heart in \add the\add* messiah.
